title: Footage released of two men wanted over Ipswich rape
text:
Media playback is unsupported on your device Footage released of two men wanted over Ipswich rape 3 March 2017 Last updated at 13:52 GMT 
Footage has been released of two men police want to trace after a woman was raped, physically assaulted and left unconscious. 
The woman, in her late 20s, was attacked in Rope Walk, Ipswich at about 03:10 GMT on 25 February. 
She was grabbed by two unknown men and had her mouth covered, before being forced into a nearby car park. 
Police said the attack was thought to have lasted several minutes.
